Duties




This recruitment is open until filled. Applications received for this job opportunity will be reviewed immediately. Your prompt response is encouraged. The hiring manager reserves the right to make a hiring decision at any time during the recruitment process.

As the Management Analyst 4 in the Information Services Division (ISD), you will provide professional advice and consultation, using research, analysis, planning, project management, and facilitate information sharing with internal and external stakeholders. You will function as a specialist regarding highly complex issues that have a broad scope and impact on outside agencies, partner organizations and customers. You will also manage assigned projects that have agency-wide and interagency impacts.

Some of the duties you will perform include:



Providing technical support to the DRS IT Services, Portfolio and Planning Manager;
Serving as lead for fiscal notes during legislative sessions;
Ensuring DRS is compliant with State and Federal requirements;
Guiding assigned projects with agency-wide and interagency impact;
Leading the coordination and completion of performance management activities for the division;
Planning, preparing and producing complex reports and presentations for use by the Leadership Team and other agency leaders by combining multiple data sources to create data models;
Developing and maintaining ISD product management quarterly roadmap in coordination with the IT Services, Portfolio and Planning Manager;
Researching, analyzing and providing recommendations for improvement to processes and tools; and
Coordinating between external entities and the agency to ensure required documentation is provided, questions are answered, and changes are documented for future compliance efforts.

NOTE: Dependent on the nature of the projects and tasks assigned, you may be able to perform duties from a remote work location on a full-time basis; however, you must be willing and able to adjust your telework schedule at any time to attend mandatory meetings, trainings, receive IT support, etc., at the DRS building. To be eligible for remote work, you must:

Have a telework agreement in place approved by the Appointing Authority;
Live within a reasonable commuting distance (less than 50 straight-line miles) to the DRS building in Tumwater, WA; and
Have a remote work environment that is both safe and has an appropriate level of connectivity.



Qualifications




Qualifications For This Position Include:



A minimum of five (5) years of experience conducting research and analysis of statistical data and trends (an Associate’s or Bachelor’s degree in mathematics, statistics, information technology or closely allied field may substitute for up to two years of experience);
A minimum of three (3) years of experience leading business projects, to include utilizing business analysis tools and methodologies to elicit and develop requirements;
Experience with process improvement principles and methodologies (e.g., Lean, Six Sigma);
Experience managing change, facilitating collaboration and leading teams;
Experience researching and analyzing state and agency laws, policies, standards and regulations to draft required technology and business governance; and
Demonstrated advanced-level proficiency with Microsoft Productivity Suite and SharePoint (version 2013 or newer).

Preferred/Desired Qualifications:

A bachelor’s degree or higher in mathematics, statistics, information technology, or other closely allied field;
Lean Six Sigma Green Belt certification;
Strong analytical, problem solving, decision making and consultative skills;
Proven ability to communicate effectively, both orally and in writing, to articulate complex information in easily understandable terms and make presentations to senior leadership and external parties;
Strong commitment to customer service; and
Demonstrated proficiency in the following competency areas:

Analysis
Studies and reviews documents and information closely; readily identifies information that is not pertinent and understands when additional or verifying data is needed. Uses data and information in a clear and rational thought process to assess and understand issues, evaluate options, form accurate conclusions and make recommendations/decisions.

Communication
Effectively conveys information in writing and through the spoken word, using language that is appropriate to both the complexity of the topic and the knowledge and understanding of the audience. Sees communication as a vital component of high performing teams.

Coordinating and Organizing
Effectively organizes work and coordinates activities, services and schedules to ensure smooth and efficient operation of work. Is an effective communications link and reliable source of information for others. Keeps interested parties informed of the status of events.

Mathematical Reasoning
Familiar and comfortable working with numbers. Understands how numbers are related, combined and estimated; accurately executes arithmetical calculations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication and division. Quickly recognizes when the results of a mathematical operation are inconsistent with expectations and detects probable errors in calculations.

Results Orientation/Initiative
Focuses on results and desired outcomes and how best to achieve them. Identifies what needs to be done and proactively does it before being asked to or required by the situation. Takes on responsibilities and challenges; plans for upcoming problems or opportunities and takes appropriate action.

Commitment to Diversity
Recognizes the value of diversity. Helps create an environment that embraces and supports diversity, equity and inclusion.



